File: COVID-19 test. AFP/Jens Schlueter JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 339 new COVID-19 deaths. The Western Cape recorded the most deaths at 142, with the Eastern Cape following with 107. READ: Coronavirus in SA: Ramaphosa announces measures to curb second wave The death toll now stands at over 25,246. An additional 9,501 new COVID-19 cases have been recorded. Taking the total to over 940,000. Over 800,000 people have recovered. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.